{"type":null,"faqId":36223,"title":"The connection is frequently lost when connecting to the Internet via mobile data","answer":"<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Connect to the Internet in an area with a stronger mobile data\nsignal.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Go to <b>Settings</b>,\nselect <b>Mobile networks</b> (EMUI 2.0 and\nEMUI 2.3) or <b>More &gt; Mobile networks</b>\n(EMUI 3.0) and then select the <b>Enable\nalways-on mobile data</b> check box.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Go to <b>Settings</b> and\nselect <b>Mobile networks &gt; Access Point\nNames</b> (EMUI 2.0 and EMUI 2.3) or <b>More\n&gt; Mobile networks &gt; Access Point Names</b> (EMUI 3.0).</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char;'>Check with your network provider that the access point\nname (APN) parameters are correct. You can view the current access points by\nselecting <b>Mobile networks &gt; Access\nPoint Names</b>.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>If you still cannot resolve the issue after trying the steps\nabove, you are recommended to restart your phone or restore your phone to factory\nsettings after backing up important data.</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"1248","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1438759299000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":21,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Internet connection drops frequently, mobile data","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}